verbose_text: The most important among them are the junctional adhesion molecule like protein JAML, CD100 (also known as semaphorin 4D), and NKG2D receptors, which interact with the coxsackie and adenovirus receptor, plexin B2, and a group of stress inducible MHC class I like molecules known as NKG2D ligands, respectively.
